  "help": "Help",
  "helpTitle": "Help & FAQ",
  "helpSubtitle": "Find answers to common questions about every feature in Agatha Track.",

  "faqAccountTitle": "Account & Authentication",
  "faqAccountQ1": "How do I create an account?",
  "faqAccountA1": "Tap \"Sign Up\" on the landing page. Enter your email address, choose a password, and provide your first and last name. You will be logged in automatically after signing up.",
  "faqAccountQ2": "How do I log in?",
  "faqAccountA2": "Tap \"Log In\" on the landing page and enter your email and password. Your session stays active until you log out.",
  "faqAccountQ3": "I forgot my password — how do I reset it?",
  "faqAccountA3": "On the login screen, tap \"Forgot password?\". Enter the email address associated with your account and follow the instructions to set a new password.",
  "faqAccountQ4": "How do I update my profile?",
  "faqAccountA4": "Go to the user menu (your avatar in the top-right corner), then tap \"My Details\". From there you can edit your name, bio, profile photo, and change your password.",
  "faqAccountQ5": "How do I log out?",
  "faqAccountA5": "Open the user menu (avatar icon in the top-right corner) and tap \"Logout\". You will be returned to the landing page.",

  "faqPetProfileTitle": "Pet Profiles",
  "faqPetProfileQ1": "How do I add a new pet?",
  "faqPetProfileA1": "Tap the \"+\" button on the main pet list screen. Fill in your pet's name, species, breed, date of birth, and optional details like microchip number and photo. Each pet is assigned a unique colour for easy identification.",
  "faqPetProfileQ2": "How do I edit or delete a pet?",
  "faqPetProfileA2": "Tap on the pet's card to open its detail page. Use the edit icon in the top-right to update information. To delete a pet, use the delete option — note that deleting a pet permanently removes all associated health entries, weight records, and other data.",
  "faqPetProfileQ3": "What does the identification reminder mean?",
  "faqPetProfileA3": "If your pet does not have an ID (microchip or tag number) recorded, a species-specific reminder will appear on the pet's card. You can dismiss this reminder or add the ID in the pet's edit form.",
  "faqPetProfileQ4": "How do I mark a pet as passed away?",
  "faqPetProfileA4": "Open the pet's edit form and enable the \"Passed away\" option. This changes the pet's colour to white, adds a memorial overlay to the photo, and sends a notification. The pet remains in your list as a memorial.",
  "faqPetProfileQ5": "What is the pet colour system?",
  "faqPetProfileA5": "Each pet is assigned a unique colour from a palette of 15 colours when created. This colour appears on cards, charts, and throughout the app to help you quickly identify each pet at a glance.",
  "faqPetProfileQ6": "How is my pet's age calculated?",
  "faqPetProfileA6": "Age is automatically calculated from the date of birth you enter. It updates dynamically and is displayed on the pet's detail page and profile cards.",

  "faqHealthTitle": "Health Tracking",
  "faqHealthQ1": "What types of health entries can I track?",
  "faqHealthA1": "You can track medications, preventive treatments (vaccinations, deworming, flea/tick treatments), vet visits, and medical procedures. Each type has its own icon and colour in the dashboard.",
  "faqHealthQ2": "How do I add a health entry?",
  "faqHealthA2": "You can add entries from two places: the pet's detail page (specific to that pet) or the global Health Dashboard (accessible from the medical icon in the top bar). Fill in the type, name, date, and optional details like frequency, notes, and photo attachments.",
  "faqHealthQ3": "What is the Health Dashboard?",
  "faqHealthA3": "The Health Dashboard is a global view of all health events across all your pets. It is organised into tabs by type (medications, preventives, vet visits, etc.) and shows upcoming, due, and overdue entries. You can filter by organisation to focus on specific groups of pets.",
  "faqHealthQ4": "How do recurring health entries work?",
  "faqHealthA4": "When creating a health entry, you can set a frequency (e.g., daily, weekly, monthly, yearly, or a custom number of days). The app will automatically schedule the next occurrence and notify you when it is due.",
  "faqHealthQ5": "What are Health Issues?",
  "faqHealthA5": "Health Issues let you track ongoing medical conditions (e.g., allergies, chronic illness). Each issue can have a start date, optional end date, and can be linked to related health entries for a complete medical history.",
  "faqHealthQ6": "Can I attach photos to health entries?",
  "faqHealthA6": "Yes. When creating or editing a health entry, you can attach a photo — for example, a picture of a prescription, lab results, or a wound. The photo is stored with the entry and visible on the detail view.",

  "faqWeightTitle": "Weight Tracking",
  "faqWeightQ1": "How do I record my pet's weight?",
  "faqWeightA1": "Open the pet's detail page and scroll to the Weight section. Tap the add button to enter a new weight reading. You can choose between kilograms (kg) and pounds (lb).",
  "faqWeightQ2": "How is weight data displayed?",
  "faqWeightA2": "Weight history is shown as an interactive line chart on the pet's detail page. You can see trends over time and tap individual data points for details. The chart uses your pet's unique colour.",
  "faqWeightQ3": "Can I switch between kg and lb?",
  "faqWeightA3": "Yes. Use the unit toggle on the weight section to switch between kilograms and pounds. The conversion is applied to all displayed values.",

  "faqVetTitle": "Veterinarian Management",
  "faqVetQ1": "How do I add a veterinarian?",
  "faqVetA1": "Go to the Veterinarians section (accessible from the stethoscope icon in the top bar). Tap the \"+\" button and fill in the clinic name, vet name, phone number, email, address, and website.",
  "faqVetQ2": "How do I link a vet to my pet?",
  "faqVetA2": "When editing a pet's profile, you can select a veterinarian from your saved list. This links the vet to the pet so their contact information is readily available on the pet's detail page.",
  "faqVetQ3": "Can I edit or delete a vet?",
  "faqVetA3": "Yes. From the Veterinarians list, tap on a vet to view their details, then use the edit or delete options. Deleting a vet removes the link from any associated pets but does not delete the pets themselves.",

  "faqSharingTitle": "Pet Sharing",
  "faqSharingQ1": "How do I share a pet with someone?",
  "faqSharingA1": "Open the pet's detail page and use the share option to generate a share link. Send this link to the person you want to share with. When they accept, they will see the pet in their list.",
  "faqSharingQ2": "What happens when someone accepts a share?",
  "faqSharingA2": "The recipient receives a notification with the pending share. They can choose to place the shared pet into their personal list or into an organisation they belong to. The pet appears with a \"shared\" badge.",
  "faqSharingQ3": "Can I hide a shared pet?",
  "faqSharingA3": "Yes. Swipe left on a shared pet's card to hide it. Hidden pets will not appear in your pet list, health dashboard, or generate notifications. You can unhide them from the organisation's detail page under \"Hidden Shared Pets\".",
  "faqSharingQ4": "What is the difference between sharing and transferring?",
  "faqSharingA4": "Sharing gives someone view access to a pet — the original owner retains full control. Transferring (available for organisation pets) moves ownership of the pet to another user or organisation entirely.",

  "faqOrgTitle": "Organisations",
  "faqOrgQ1": "What are organisations for?",
  "faqOrgA1": "Organisations let multiple people collaborate on pet care. They are ideal for vet clinics, shelters, charities, and foster networks. You can create Professional or Charity organisations.",
  "faqOrgQ2": "How do I create an organisation?",
  "faqOrgA2": "Go to the Organisations page (accessible from the business icon in the top bar or from My Details). Tap \"Create\" and choose Professional or Charity, then fill in the name and details. You become the super user automatically.",
  "faqOrgQ3": "How do I invite people to my organisation?",
  "faqOrgA3": "From the organisation's detail page, tap \"Add User\". Enter the person's email address and choose their role — either \"Member\" or \"Super User\". They will receive a pending invite they can accept or decline.",
  "faqOrgQ4": "What is the difference between a Member and a Super User?",
  "faqOrgA4": "Members can view and manage pets within the organisation. Super Users have additional permissions: they can invite or remove members, edit organisation details, transfer pets, and manage archives.",
  "faqOrgQ5": "How do I archive or restore a pet in an organisation?",
  "faqOrgA5": "Super Users can archive a pet from the organisation's pet list (e.g., after an adoption). Archived pets are hidden from the active list but preserved for record-keeping. They can be restored at any time from the Archived Pets section.",

  "faqFamilyEventsTitle": "Family Events",
  "faqFamilyEventsQ1": "What are Family Events?",
  "faqFamilyEventsA1": "Family Events are care assignments for organisation pets. They record who is responsible for a pet during a specific period — such as a foster stay or temporary care. Each event has an assigned member, date range, and optional notes.",
  "faqFamilyEventsQ2": "How do I create a Family Event?",
  "faqFamilyEventsA2": "Open an organisation pet's detail page and scroll to the Family Events section. Tap the add button, choose the assigned member, set the from and optional to dates, and add any notes. All organisation members will be notified.",
  "faqFamilyEventsQ3": "Do Family Events appear in the Health Dashboard?",
  "faqFamilyEventsA3": "Yes. Family Events have their own dedicated tab in the Health Dashboard. They also trigger reminder notifications when an event's end date is approaching, so all organisation members stay informed.",

  "faqNotificationsTitle": "Notifications",
  "faqNotificationsQ1": "What notifications will I receive?",
  "faqNotificationsA1": "You will receive in-app notifications for: due or overdue health entries, upcoming medication reminders, organisation invites, share requests, pet memorials, and family event reminders.",
  "faqNotificationsQ2": "How do I manage notification preferences?",
  "faqNotificationsA2": "Go to the Notifications screen (bell icon in the top bar) and tap the settings icon. From there you can customise which types of notifications you receive.",
  "faqNotificationsQ3": "Can I mute notifications for a specific pet?",
  "faqNotificationsA3": "Yes. Each pet has a mute option in its notification settings. Muted pets will not generate any health-related notifications until unmuted.",
  "faqNotificationsQ4": "Can I snooze a notification?",
  "faqNotificationsA4": "Yes. You can snooze individual notifications to be reminded again after a chosen number of days. The snoozed reminder will reappear counting from today, not from the original due date.",

  "faqReportsTitle": "Reports",
  "faqReportsQ1": "How do I generate a pet report?",
  "faqReportsA1": "Open a pet's detail page and tap the report/PDF icon. You can customise what to include — profile information, weight history, health events, health issues, family events, notifications, and sharing details. The report is generated as a downloadable PDF.",
  "faqReportsQ2": "What information is included in a report?",
  "faqReportsA2": "Reports can include: pet profile details (name, breed, age, ID), a weight chart and history table, a list of all health entries by type, recorded health issues, family event assignments and foster stays (for organisation pets), recent notifications and alerts, and sharing access details. You choose which sections to include before generating.",

  "faqSubscriptionTitle": "Subscription",
  "faqSubscriptionQ1": "Is Agatha Track free to use?",
  "faqSubscriptionA1": "Agatha Track offers a free tier with core features. An optional premium subscription unlocks additional capabilities and removes limits. Visit the Subscription page from My Details to learn more.",
  "faqSubscriptionQ2": "How do I subscribe?",
  "faqSubscriptionA2": "Go to My Details and tap \"Subscription\". Choose a plan and complete the purchase through your platform's payment system. Your subscription is managed securely through RevenueCat.",
  "faqSubscriptionQ3": "How do I cancel my subscription?",
  "faqSubscriptionA3": "Subscriptions can be managed or cancelled through your device's app store settings (App Store or Google Play). Changes take effect at the end of the current billing period.",

  "faqLanguageTitle": "Language & Accessibility",
  "faqLanguageQ1": "How do I change the app language?",
  "faqLanguageA1": "Go to My Details and use the language dropdown to switch between English and French. The change takes effect immediately across the entire app and is saved to your profile.",
  "faqLanguageQ2": "Is the app accessible?",
  "faqLanguageA2": "Yes. Agatha Track includes accessibility features throughout: semantic labels for screen readers, tooltips on all interactive elements, proper form field labelling, and keyboard navigation support."
}
